nt des traits multiples qui ne reflètent plus la seule fidélité et la ressemblance au passé mais surtout une volonté, énergique et irréversible, d'adaptation aux exigences d'une civilisation moderne ouverte sur l'univers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFrench-Canadians. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Advocacy.2bisacsh1 aLamontagne, Leopold, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999z978311049094740uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148757549640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487575496423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487575496.jpg  a978-3-11-049094-7  University of Toronto Press eBook-Package Archive 1933-1999c1933d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK